Project Context:
This is an End-to-End test automation framework validating a PHP PowerDNS library using:
- Java (TestNG + RestAssured)
- PHP bridge layer (bridge.php via built-in server)
- PowerDNS API backend
- Allure reporting

Core Principles:
- Maintain clear separation between:
  - Test Layer (Java TestNG)
  - API Client Layer (RestAssured)
  - Bridge Layer (PHP)
- Do NOT mix test assertions with request-building logic
- Ensure tests remain deterministic and repeatable
    - Use dynamic test data where possible

Coding Rules:
- Follow Page Object Model equivalent for APIs (API Client abstraction)
- Avoid hardcoding test data except where defined in specification
- Use reusable request/response builders
- Prefer explicit validation over implicit assumptions
- Avoid duplicated logic across tests

Stability Rules:
- Do NOT introduce flaky constructs (e.g., Thread.sleep)
- Ensure idempotent test design (safe re-runs)
- Tests must clean up created zones where applicable

Modification Rules:
- Preserve existing architecture
- Do NOT refactor large sections unless explicitly requested
- Make minimal, safe, reviewable changes

Security Rules:
- Do NOT expose API keys in logs or reports unless masked